article.headline: UC Irvine 65, Idaho 63
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- UC Irvine's Jeff Gloger made a game-winning jumper at the final buzzer as the Anteaters, who led by 20 points in the first half, needed a late rally to beat Idaho 65-63 Thursday night. Ross Schraeder scored a career-high 27 points and Adam Parada added 14 for the Anteaters (11-14, 6-9 Big West Conference), who had lost eight of nine going into the game. Tyrone Hayes scored 14 points for the Vandals (12-14, 8-8), whose three-game winning streak ended. Rashaad Powell added 12 points and Dwayne Williams had 11 points. Irvine held a 36-16 lead with 3:07 left in the first half but Idaho rallied to move ahead 62-61 on Lionel Davis's jumper with 48 seconds to play. Parada's hook shot with 18 seconds left put the Anteaters ahead by one point. Davis tied the score by making the second of two free throws with 9.3 seconds remaining. After Irvine's Greg Ethington inbounded the ball, Gloger took a pass from Matt Okoro, dribbled into the frontcourt and made a 16-foot jumper. Gloger finished with nine points. Irvine played without starter Mike Efevberha, who has been suspended indefinitely for violating team and athletic department rules, the university announced Wednesday.
